This recipe is fantastic and super easy. The title is misleading since it is really a sheet cake, rather than a bar. I have made this cake with the exact recipe, as well as substituted GF flour, used half melted butter/half oil when I didn't have enough oil, and cut the sugar by 1/2 cup. It always comes out wonderfully. I haven't made the frosting but usually dust with sugar or make a quick maple glaze. This is my go to fall recipe when I have to make something last minute!

