Rating: 0
I have a similar recipe but it's in storage due to a recent international move. I've been using that recipe for over 20 years! My niece requested them as her birthday falls on October 31 so I searched the net to find a recipe like mine and this is the closest I've come. I've made some changes to the original recipe I used. I use the light raisins instead of the dark raisins. I think they have a better flavor. I also add a cup of chopped walnuts to the bars and I put 3 or 4 tablespoons of pure maple syrup in the cream cheese frosting. After I frost the bars, I sprinkle chopped walnuts on the cream cheese. Scrumptious and they are always a favorite at church potlucks!!

Rating: 3
Really moist and flavorful bar/cake. I did, however, make a few relatively minor changes...I used oat flour (instead of AP), 3/4 cup of dark brown sugar (instead of 2 cups white), 1/2 cup applesauce + 1/4 cup olive oil (instead of the 3/4 cup oil) and fat free cream cheese in the frosting. I know, it sounds like a lot of changes..but really pretty standard, healthier substitutions. Even with the decrease in sugar it's still pretty sweet. The pumpkin and spice ratio lend well to using whole grain flours (whole wheat, spelt, oat, etc.) without noticing the difference. The frosting was yummy, even with the FF cream cheese. Overall a very versatile and adaptable recipe for those of us who like to fool around with the originals. Oh, I also left out the raisins. I gave it 3 forks, only b/c I changed it up and the original recipe had 2 cups of sugar, (not including the other cup in the frosting)..overkill, anyone?!. With changes I rate it at 4 forks:)

