Rating: 0
I've been making for 28 years a similar recipe that people love: 4 eggs; 1 c.veg. oil; 2 c. sugar; 1 c. pumpkin; 2 c. flour; 1 tsp baking powder; 1 tsp. baking soda; 1/2 tsp. salt; 2 tsp. cinnamon; 1 cup pecans. Combine all ingredients. Bake 350 in a greased, floured 15" jelly roll pan, 20-25 minutes. Frosting: 3 oz. cream cheese; 6 Tblsp. butter; 3/4 lb. powdered sugar; 1 tsp. vanilla; a very little milk for spreadability. Spread on warm cake. Chill before cutting into bars.

